    <text id="F0669T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Sweigart tells his cousin that his regiment is close to Richmond and will attack
                    it very soon. He also describes the atrocities that the rebels have committed
                    and discusses a family matter.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Cousin</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1862-07-24">July the 24 1862 </date>
                        <name type="place">
                            <sic corr="Virginia">Verginia</sic>
                        </name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear <orig reg="Cousin">Cosin</orig>
                    </salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I <orig reg="received">reseavd</orig> your <orig reg="civil">civill</orig>
                    <orig reg="and">an</orig>
                    <orig reg="welcome">welkom</orig>
                    <orig reg="letter">lettar</orig> and was very glad <orig reg="indeed"
                    >indead</orig> to hear from <orig reg="you all">yous aul</orig>. <orig reg="We"
                        >Whe</orig> are within 30 miles of <orig reg="Richmond">Ritchma</orig> and
                    expect to <orig reg="attack">atact</orig> the Rebels at <orig reg="Richmond"
                        >Ritchmond</orig> in 4 or 5 <orig reg="days">dayes</orig>. i think <orig
                        reg="there">their</orig> will be <orig reg="some">som</orig>
                    <orig reg="fighting">fiting</orig>
                    <orig reg="done">don</orig>
                    <orig reg="there">their</orig> but our <orig reg="cause">cos</orig> is just. i
                    must be done and <orig reg="am">an</orig> bound to <orig reg="see">se</orig> it
                    through. the Rebels are <orig reg="worse">wors</orig>
                    <orig reg="than">then</orig>
                    <pb/> a set of <orig reg="heathens">heathren</orig>. they take our men and pin
                    them up <orig reg="against">aganst</orig>
                    <orig reg="trees">treas</orig> with their <orig reg="bayonettes">buynetts</orig>
                    and fire upon our hospitals <orig reg="where">wheir</orig> the sick are. <orig
                        reg="And">An</orig> they have fired on <orig reg="several">severails</orig>
                    of our <orig reg="flags">flag</orig> of truth and <orig reg="when">whe</orig> it
                    comes to that <unclear>
                        <orig reg="roust">roust</orig>
                    </unclear> i <orig reg="think">thik</orig> it is time to <orig reg="do">du</orig>
                    <orig reg="something">somthig</orig> it <orig reg="raises">rais</orig> my <orig
                        reg="blood">blud</orig>
                    <orig reg="every">evry</orig> time i see <orig reg="such">sutch</orig> things. i
                    have <orig reg="seen">seem</orig> more <orig reg="than">then</orig> i ever
                    expect to see and more <orig reg="than">then</orig> ever i want to see again.
                    general pope has <orig reg="given">gaven</orig> orders to take <orig reg="every"
                        >evry</orig>
                    <pb/> thing <orig reg="we">Whe</orig> want of the farmers and <orig reg="we"
                    >whe</orig> will <orig reg="do">du</orig> so. i think the rebels will not get
                        <orig reg="much">mutch</orig> on the ground. <orig reg="We">Whe</orig> have
                        <orig reg="gone">went</orig> over that <unclear>
                        <orig reg="ought to have been">ought of bean</orig>
                    </unclear>
                    <orig reg="done">dun</orig>
                    <orig reg="sooner">suner</orig> and the rebels supply would not be so great when
                    ever <orig reg="we">whe</orig> had to <unclear>
                        <orig reg="return">retied</orig>
                    </unclear> Why the rebels got their supplies by that is over and <orig
                        reg="though">tho</orig> the war is not over yet and i <orig reg="think"
                    >thik</orig> 1 year will not end it but i am bound to see it As far as i can.
                    uncle david said that <orig reg="all">aul</orig> was <orig reg="right"
                    >rite</orig>. he <orig reg="doesn't">doant</orig>
                    <orig reg="think">thik</orig> hard <orig reg="at all">ataul</orig> of <unclear>
                        <orig reg="you">youns</orig>
                    </unclear>
                    <orig reg="at all">ataul</orig>. he will lend you the money if he <orig
                        reg="doesn't">doant</orig> come home till august. he <orig
                        reg="has promised">is promist</orig> again that time his <orig
                        reg="discharge">discharg</orig>. i am in a <orig reg="hurry">hury</orig>.
                    you must excuse bad <orig reg="writing">riting</orig>. i can not <orig
                        reg="write">rite</orig>
                    <orig reg="much">mutch</orig> this time. i will <orig reg="write">rite</orig>
                    more next time. <orig reg="write">rite</orig> soon. </p>
                <closer>
                    <salute> </salute>
                    <signed>J. B. Sweigart </signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
